RIYADH: Saudi Islamic real estate financier Amlak International has appointed Abdullah bin Turki Al-Sudairy as managing director, in addition to his current CEO position. Al-Sudairy has served as the company’s CEO since 2007 and has a wide range of experience in the financial sector, according to a bourse filing. The Saudi-listed company said it received the Saudi central bank’s no-objection on April 21. Amlak, regulated by the Saudi central bank, offers a range of financing solutions to institutions, high net worth individuals, and real estate developers.